When to Use This
Use the Traditional/Industry-Standard CMS Forwarders when your monitoring workflow depends on
established alarm-receiver formats or legacy integration methods.
1. When your organization uses a traditional national or regional CMS infrastructure
Many national CMS operators still rely on hardware alarm receivers or long-established protocols.
This option ensures Genesis events integrate seamlessly with those environments.
2. When you need compatibility with existing CMS platforms (IMMIX, ATS, AMWIN, LISA, etc.)
https://helpdesk.nxgen.io/support/nxgentechnology/ShowHomePage.do#Solutions/dv/17599000024320439/en
Choose this category when your backend requires:
SMTP email ingestion (e.g., IMMIX)
DC-09 alarm frames (e.g., ATS D09, AMWIN DC09, LISA custom D09)
3. When migrating gradually from legacy CMS to modern cloud architecture
This option supports hybrid environments where:
The customer continues using legacy CMS receivers
Genesis delivers alarms in backward-compatible formats
Migration can happen at their own pace without interruption
Genesis normalizes all events and converts them into protocol-compliant frames expected by each CMS.
Technological Alarm Forwarders
Modern, flexible, API-friendly distribution channels
Overview
These integrations are designed for customers who want to:
Organizations building their own CMS or working with technology partners who use customized
monitoring platforms.
Feed alarms into automation platforms (Node-RED, Azure Logic Apps, n8n, Zapier).
Store alarms in external systems or data lakes.
Integrate non-CMS business applications.
