Configuration - Alarm Forwarder
The Genesis platform allows customers to route alarms and events to different backend systems through a
flexible, JSON-based configuration.
Each forwarder type—Webhook, File Transfer, Email (SMTP), and MQTT—supports its own configuration
block with customizable properties and retry policies. It can be configurable in Service
Provider/Customer/Site/Device level.
This section explains each field in detail so customers can configure their integrations safely and correctly.
https://helpdesk.nxgen.io/support/nxgentechnology/ShowHomePage.do#Solutions/dv/17599000024320439/en
Webhook Forwarder Configuration
Webhooks enable real-time delivery of alarms to any HTTP/HTTPS endpoint.
1. "webhook": {
2.   "type": "webhook",
3.   "properties": {
4.     "url": "https://customer-endpoint.com/alarms",
5.     "method": "POST",
6.     "auth": {
7.       "type": "none | basic | digest | bearer | apiKey | custom",
8.       "basic": { "username": "", "password": "" },
9.       "digest": { "username": "", "password": "" },
10.       "bearer": { "token": "" },
11.       "apiKey": {
12.         "location": "header | query",
13.         "keyName": "X-API-Key",
14.         "keyValue": "123456"
15.       },
16.       "customHeaders": {
https://helpdesk.nxgen.io/support/nxgentechnology/ShowHomePage.do#Solutions/dv/17599000024320439/en
17.         "X-Custom-1": "value1",
18.         "X-Custom-2": "value2"
19.       }
20.     },
21.     "payloadTemplate": "{ \"event\": \"{{eventType}}\", \"timestamp\": \"{{timestamp}}\" }",
22.     "attachment": {
23.       "enabled": false,
24.       "fileFormat": "mp4",
25.       "filenameTemplate": "{{siteName}}_{{deviceName}}_{{cameraName}}_{{eventType}}"
26.     }
27.   },
28.   "retry_policy": {
29.     "max_retries": 3,
30.     "retry_interval_sec": 10
31.   }
32. }
Configuration Breakdown
Name
Description
url
Destination endpoint URL where alarms are delivered.
method
HTTP method used. Supported: POST
auth
Authentication Options:
none - No authentication.
basic - Standard username/password Base64 auth.
digest - Digest challenge-response used by some legacy systems.
bearer - Token-based authorization (e.g., JWT, Auth0 static tokens, etc..)
apiKey - API Key sent via header or query parameter.
custom - Allows sending arbitrary custom headers.
payloadTemplate
A templated JSON body. Genesis will replace variables like {{eventType}},
{{timestamp}}, {{siteName}}, etc.
Example: payloadTemplate: "{ \"event\": \"{{eventType}}\", \"timestamp\": \"
{{timestamp}}\" }"
Attachment Options
enabled - Whether to attach media (snapshot/video).
fileFormat - mp4, jpeg.
filenameTemplate - Dynamic naming based on event metadata.
https://helpdesk.nxgen.io/support/nxgentechnology/ShowHomePage.do#Solutions/dv/17599000024320439/en
Retry Policy
If the webhook server fails (5xx, timeout), Genesis retries:
max_retries - Number of attempts before failure.
retry_interval_sec - Delay between attempts.
File Transfer Forwarder Configuration
Used when a CMS or backend system ingests files via FTP/FTPS.
1. "filetransfer": {
2.   "type": "file_transfer",
3.   "properties": {
4.     "protocol": "ftp | ftps",
5.     "host": "file.customer.com",
6.     "port": 21,
7.     "username": "alarm_user",
8.     "password": "xxxx",
9.     "secure": false,
10.     "path": "/incoming/alarms",
11.     "fileFormat": "mp4",
12.     "filenameTemplate": "alarm-{{eventId}}"
13.   },
14.   "retry_policy": {
15.     "max_retries": 5,
16.     "retry_interval_sec": 30
17.   }
18. }
Configuration Breakdown
Name
Description
protocol
ftp - Standard FTP
ftsp - FTP with TLS
secure
If true, forces FTPS explicit TLS mode.
path
Directory where files are uploaded.
https://helpdesk.nxgen.io/support/nxgentechnology/ShowHomePage.do#Solutions/dv/17599000024320439/en
File Output
fileFormat - mp4, jpg.
filenameTemplate - Template-driven dynamic filenames.
Email Forwarder Configuration
Sends alarms to email recipients, often used for older monitoring systems such as IMMIX.
1. "email": {
2.   "type": "smtp",
3.   "properties": {
4.     "to": ["ops-team@customer.com"],
5.     "subjectTemplate": "Alarm - {{eventType}} at {{siteName}}",
6.     "bodyTemplate": "Alarm: {{eventType}} occurred at {{timestamp}}.",
7.     "attachment": {
8.       "enabled": false,
9.       "fileFormat": "jpg",
10.       "filenameTemplate": "{{eventId}}_snapshot"
11.     }
12.   },
13.   "retry_policy": {
14.     "max_retries": 5,
15.     "retry_interval_sec": 60
16.   }
17. }
Configuration Breakdown
Name
Description
to
Recipients
Templates
Support templating for full customization.
subjectTemplate, bodyTemplate
Attachment block
Same structure as Webhook forwarder.
MQTT Forwarder Configuration
https://helpdesk.nxgen.io/support/nxgentechnology/ShowHomePage.do#Solutions/dv/17599000024320439/en
Used for IoT platforms, real-time event buses, and custom CMS systems.
1. "mqtt": {
2.   "type": "mqtt",
3.   "properties": {
4.     "brokerUrl": "mqtt://broker.customer.com:1883",
5.     "username": "mqtt_user",
6.     "password": "xxxx",
7.     "topic": "alarms/{{siteId}}",
8.     "qos": 1,
9.     "retain": false,
10.     "payloadTemplate": "{ \"event\": \"{{eventType}}\", \"timestamp\": \"{{timestamp}}\", \"device\": \"
{{deviceName}}\" }"
11.   },
12.   "retry_policy": {
13.     "max_retries": 10,
14.     "retry_interval_sec": 5
15.   }
16. }
Configuration Breakdown
Name
Description
brokerUrl
mqtt:// and ws:// (MQTT over websockets) based broker url
topic
Fully template-based topic routing, e.g.: alarms/tower-{{siteId}}/device-
{{deviceId}}
QoS Levels
 0 - fire and forget, 1 - Atleast Once, 2 - Exactly Once
Payload Template
JSON payloads with dynamic fields.
