Detailed Use Cases
Below are the derived explanations of what each scenario represents in real customer deployments.
1. Existing Evalink Talos Customer (Cloud-Only Customer)
Primary = Talos | Traditional = None | Technological = Webhook
Who is this for?
Customers who already run their monitoring operations on Evalink Talos and want Genesis to seamlessly feed
alarms, AI events, and device health to their Talos environment.
Use Case Description
Customer operates fully in the cloud and does not use any legacy receivers or DC-09 infrastructure.
Genesis acts as the tower/device/AI processing layer, while Talos remains the operator console and
workflow engine.
Optional: Technological forwarders (Webhook, API, MQTT) may be used for analytics, automation, or
forwarding events to third-party tools.
Typical Customer Example
A global cloud-first monitoring company using Talos for all operator workflows, wanting Genesis to integrate
video alarms, AI metadata, and tower telemetry directly into Talos in real time.
2. Customer Migrating from AmWin/ATS/Legacy CMS to Talos
(Legacy CMS Migration + Cloud Future)
Primary = None → later Talos | Traditional = ATS/AmWin | Technological = None
https://helpdesk.nxgen.io/support/nxgentechnology/ShowHomePage.do#Solutions/dv/17599000024320439/en
Who is this for?
Organizations using legacy CMS systems such as ATS or AmWin and slowly transitioning to cloud-native
solutions like Evalink Talos.
Use Case Description
Customer still relies on traditional DC-09 receivers for their current alarm workflow.
Genesis sends alarms in ATS D09, AmWin DC-09, or custom D09 formats during the transition.
Once migration completes, the customer switches Primary = Talos.
Typical Customer Example
A nationwide CMS using ATS hardware receivers migrating their sites in phases to Talos.
During transition:
Traditional alarms → ATS receiver
AI events + IoT telemetry → Talos and validate in parallel.
Future: Everything consolidated into Talos and turn off ATS.
3. Hybrid Monitoring Setup (Talos + IMMIX + Technological Services)
Primary = Talos | Traditional = IMMIX | Technological = Email or Webhook
Who is this for?
Large enterprises or bureau operators running multiple CMS platforms in parallel.
Use Case Description
Evalink Talos handles advanced cloud monitoring, collaboration, and workflow automation.
IMMIX is still used for a part of their operations (e.g., remote guarding workflows).
Genesis feeds both systems simultaneously:
Talos: AI alarms, device health, tower telemetry (Primary)
IMMIX: Camera-based alarms via SMTP/Email
Technological: Extra routing via Email/Webhook for internal tools or automation
Typical Customer Example
https://helpdesk.nxgen.io/support/nxgentechnology/ShowHomePage.do#Solutions/dv/17599000024320439/en
A security-as-a-service provider with:
Talos for national operations center
IMMIX for guard-force integration and dispatch workflows
Email/Webhook for internal automation and reporting
This hybrid approach is common for customers with diverse operational units or multiple subcontractors.
4. Highly Customized / Tech-Driven Monitoring Stations (Build-their-
own CMS)
Primary = None | Traditional = None | Technological = Webhook/MQTT/File Transfer
Who is this for?
Organizations building their own monitoring backend or using a custom technology partner—not relying on any
off-the-shelf CMS.
Use Case Description
Customer builds a proprietary CMS or automation engine.
Genesis provides raw or enriched event streams via:
Webhooks for real-time event delivery
MQTT for IoT-style message pipelines
SFTP/FTP for batch processing
Email for alerting fallback
Customer has full control over how they ingest, enrich, or process alarms.
Typical Customer Example
A technology-driven monitoring provider building a fully custom cloud-native CMS using:
Webhooks to receive alarms
Their own AI engines to reprocess events
Custom dashboards for operators
No traditional CMS receiver at all
https://helpdesk.nxgen.io/support/nxgentechnology/ShowHomePage.do#Solutions/dv/17599000024320439/en
This is also common for:
Smart city platforms
Autonomous surveillance towers
Industrial automation integrators
Border/perimeter monitoring with custom workflows
https://helpdesk.nxgen.io/support/nxgentechnology/ShowHomePage.do#Solutions/dv/17599000024320439/en
